 supernova data sets are created, and it is found that the best way to\nreduce model-building uncertainties on lower-order Hubble parameters (such as\n$\\{H_{0}, q_{0}, j_{0} \\}$) is by limiting the redshift range of the data. Thus\nmore and better $z \\lesssim 1$ data, not higher-redshift data, is needed to\nsharpen cosmographic tests of flat $\\Lambda$CDM.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 Aug 2013 04:00:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 24 Aug 2014 03:51:49 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 14 Nov 2015 00:48:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-11-17"}
